quran[18]{c,v,t}:
  36,33,"And a sign for them is the dead earth. We give it life and bring out of it grain, so they eat from it"
  36,34,"And We made therein gardens of palms and vineyards, and therein We caused (some) springs to erupt forth"
  36,35,"That they may eat of their produce and what their hands have made. Will they not, then, thank (Us)"
  36,36,"All Extolment be to Him, Who created all the pairs of what the earth grows, and of themselves, and of what they do not know"
  36,37,"And a sign for them is the night; We strip the daytime from it, and so, only then they are in darkness (Literally: darksome)"
  36,38,"And the sun runs to a repository for it; that is the determining of The Ever-Mighty, the Ever-Knowing"
  36,39,"And the moon, We have determined it by phases, till it becomes again (Literally: goes back) like the old date-stalk"
  36,40,"It does not behoove the sun to overtake the moon, nor does the night outstrip the daytime, and each is swimming in an orbit"
  36,41,And a sign for them is that We carried their offspring in the laden ship (s)
  36,42,And We created for them the like of it whereon they ride
  36,43,"And in case We (so) decide, We drown them; then they will have no screaming, nor are they rescued"
  36,44,Except as a mercy from Us and enjoyment for a while
  36,45,"And when it is said to them, \"Be pious as regards what is before you (Literally: between your hands) and what is behind you, that possibly you would be granted mercy"
  36,46,"And in no way does any sign of the signs of their Lord come up to them, except that they were veering away from it"
  36,47,"And when it is said to them, \"Expend of what Allah has provided you, \" the ones who have disbelieved have said to the ones who have believed, \"Shall we feed the ones whom, if Allah decides, He will feed? Decidedly you are in nothing except evident error"
  36,48,"And they say, \"When will this promise be, in case you are sincere"
  36,49,In no way are they awaiting anything except one Shout to take them (away) as they are in constant adversaries
  36,50,"Then they will not be able to make any testament, nor will they return to their families"